results.name: Decimal expansion of proton Compton wavelength in meters.
comment: Also decimal expansion of the relativistic de Broglie wavelength of an proton whose velocity is equal to c/sqrt(2), where c is the speed of light in vacuum in SI units. For more information see A229962.
The proton Compton wavelength is the wavelength of a photon whose energy is the same as the rest energy of a proton. - _Omar E. Pol_, Dec 03 2013
